	(132,1,'2013-07-29 19:48:31','2013-07-29 19:48:31','<h1><b>Life Skills Video Curriculum: Because Education is the Key to Success</b></h1>\r\nThere are many basic subjects of everyday life that are not taught at schools.  Sometimes these subjects are explained by parents to their children, but the parents don’t always do a good job of explaining them or don’t fully understand them themselves.  Therefore many folks don’t learn these lessons until later in life, or never learn them at all.\r\n\r\n<b>SKILF</b> envisions to change that dynamic<b>.  SKILF</b> has created short video segments that teach each subject with extensive use of graphics and real life examples.  The segments are grouped by subject area and tackle issues that everyone should understand as they head out into the world.  In some cases, these Skills for Life can act as a refresher for folks who want to review a particular subject area.','Home','','inherit','open','open','','5-revision-19','','','2013-07-29 19:48:31','2013-07-29 19:48:31','',5,'http://dev.skilf.com/5-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),
	(134,1,'2013-07-26 21:15:59','2013-07-26 21:15:59','<h1>Neal Lieberman, Founder and CEO</h1>\r\n<strong>SKILF</strong> is a non-profit organization founded by Neal Lieberman in 2013.  While the idea behind <strong>SKILF</strong> first burrowed its way into Neal’s brain almost 20 years earlier, it was during more recent “teaching moments” with his 3 kids, his nanny, and his co-workers that Neal realized that it was time to create a more formal environment for sharing this kind of knowledge.\r\n\r\nNeal Lieberman is currently VP, Sales &amp; Marketing at Brain Sentry, a manufacturer of innovative helmet-mounted sensors that help identify which players should be assessed for a concussion.  An entrepreneur at both big and small companies for over 20 years, Neal previously was owner and CEO of Gifford’s Ice Cream &amp; Candy, Co., a regional ice cream manufacturer.\r\n\r\nPrior to acquiring Gifford’s, Neal spent 8 years at Discovery Channel, where as Vice President, Licensing, he licensed all of Discovery’s brands and properties across multiple industries and distribution channels. Before joining Discovery, Neal was the Director of Marketing for Bally’s Total Fitness, a national health club chain with over 325 health clubs nationwide.\r\n\r\nNeal has a Bachelor of Arts degree in Economics from Tufts University and a Master of Business Administration degree in Marketing from the Kenan-Flagler Business School at the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.  He resides in Chevy Chase, Maryland with his wife, three children and his yellow lab.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-11','','','2013-07-26 21:15:59','2013-07-26 21:15:59','',11,'http://dev.skilf.com/11-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),
