	(18,1,'2014-03-05 16:22:50','2014-03-05 16:22:50','<strong>Been there, done that.  We tap our knowledge, relationships and experience to get the job done.  </strong>\r\n\r\nThrow in creativity, strategic thinking, and boundless energy. That’s how we help clients navigate communications challenges and opportunities.\r\n\r\nKenneally Company was founded in 2004 to provide communications services for business, government and non-profit organizations.  Since that time, we have helped clients craft and deliver breakthrough communications campaigns that are aligned with “big picture” organizational goals.  \r\n\r\nSometimes that means landing a feature story in a major media outlet, creating substantive messages that stick, or fostering long-term relationships with key stakeholders.  In the end, our work helps drive the debate on your terms.  \r\n\r\nKelly Kenneally leads the company and taps a network of experienced and committed communications professionals that have the right subject matter expertise for each client.  Prior to establishing a consulting practice, Kelly served in the White House as deputy director of the President’s Commission on White House Fellowships.  She has held communications and public affairs positions at Micron Electronics, MCI WorldCom, the American Nuclear Energy Council, and public relations firms.  She began her career with the Maryland General Assembly and holds a B.A. in Government & Politics from the University of Maryland.  She is a member of the National Press Club, is a frequent speaker at conferences, and is the author of several research reports.','Experience','','publish','open','open','','experience','','','2014-03-10 17:33:47','2014-03-10 17:33:47','',0,'http://dev.kenneallycompany.com/?page_id=18',0,'page','',0),
